name: Boeing Factory Tour (Private Tour)
description:
This private experience makes your visit to the Boeing Factory truly worth your time and investment. From the moment we pick up your group in a new, private vehicle in downtown Seattle, your driver-guide will explain everything you’ll see and do during the 40-minute scenic drive north.

At the Boeing facility, you'll join the official Boeing guide for a 90-minute tour inside the factory. For seniors or guests with mobility challenges, we arrange an alternate route with no stairs, offering a flat walking path or wheelchair access when available. This option still provides the rare experience of walking inside the production line.

After the factory visit, your guide will be waiting to continue the experience—exploring the Sky Deck or the Future of Flight museum—before heading back to Seattle (a 40 to 60-minute return drive).

This is a fully private and customizable tour, perfect for travelers who want a smooth, comfortable, and enriching Boeing Factory visit.

name: Haunted Evening Seattle Pub Tour
description: This combination ghost tour and pub crawl that will take you on a walking tour to explore the fascinating history of Seattle and hear some of its most famous and creepy haunted stories. 21+ only. A costumed guide will lead tour goers on a 2-2.5 hour journey, offering glimpses into the past and revealing the stories of long-dead phantoms and specters who still call Seattle home. You'll visit three different bars, and have time to enjoy a delicious libation (at own expense) as the guide tells you about all the spooky happenings and great history of this amazing town!

review.name: Haunted Pub crawl
review.reviewBody: Super great time and our tour guide Kirsten was amazing! Super informative and the crowd was great. Discovered some new alcohol and ghostly friends so it was a night filled with spirits!

review.name: Awesome
review.reviewBody: Really great tour definitely a must just learning a little about Seattle history and finding new pubs along the way was great and Amanda was a fantastic tour guide really friendly and really knew her stuff.

review.name: Spooky Fun!
review.reviewBody: Amanda was an amazing guide and definitely made our girl’s trip even more fun! Definitely recommend for anyone wanting interesting facts and a spooky thrill.

review.name: Amazing!
review.reviewBody: Amanda was an amazing guide! She was very knowledgeable and passionate about the information she was sharing and provided knowledge about the history of Seattle, not just ghost history (which was really cool). I really enjoyed the tour and wish it was longer! She interacted with the group well and it was a very personable experience.

review.name: Awesome!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Amanda was very knowledgeable, friendly and did a great job with keeping the group together. She also provided additional historic tidbits here and there, which was really fun! I'd definitely recommend!

review.name: A Must-Do!
review.reviewBody: This tour was by far my favorite out of the ones I've done in Seattle.  For one, it's at night.  Two, ghost stories.  I mean... What more could you ask for.  And three, drinks!  😂  It's a smaller group than a lot of the other tours, which I really liked. Made it more personal.  And our guide, Kirsten, did an awesome job of being informative, interactive, and humorous along the way.  Definitely 5 stars, and I'll be doing this again and telling all my friends!

review.name: Boo
review.reviewBody: Amanda was very sweet and was informative. We did not see any ghosts during the tour. We enjoyed the 3 pups we visited.

review.name: pleasant guide, nice pubs
review.reviewBody: enjoyed the ghost stories,  a bit short, but interesting.  Our guide was excellent, but, I had the feeling the tours were set up to bring guests to the pubs.  Which is my thing anyway.    One particular thumbs down was to the pub called Tankard and Tum.  Quite an interesting visual place, especially if one likes old beer memorabilia.  Coming from Bourbon country however, I was tired of quaffing brews, so I decided to have a Kentucky bourbon.  They had none.  Which I get.  They featured local bourbons.  Not a problem.. I tried one....The bartender poured me a scant two fingers of one the Washington state finest.  The charge was $14.00.  Quite outrages in my opinion.  On a side note it was very good....but, not worth the price.  I'm used to exceptional bourbons in Kentucky which are much better and half the price.  Oh well, one lives and learns.

review.name: Great time
review.reviewBody: It was very insightful, fun, not too spooky but scary enough with the stories and ambience.  Not to mention the drinks are taken from solid bars.

review.name: Haunted Evening Seattle Pun Tour
review.reviewBody:
This was the most fun we have had. We had a great group of people on are tour. Abby was the best thank you Abby your awesome 👍😀good luck with everything
Thank you 
Chance George and Shari Brown

name: Cascadia Country Yoga Tour
description: Experience the joy and relaxation of Washington's wonders firsthand with a Yoga In The Wild tour in the beautiful North Cascades.  Combining invigorating and restorative yoga practices with exciting canyoneering adventure provides an unforgettable, once-in-a-lifetime experience.  Take a break from the daily barrage of information and discover yourself anew at one of the most beautiful, serene destinations in America.  Get the chance to explore spectacular and hidden local destinations.  See spectacular scenery, along with a unique variety of temperate plants and wildlife.

name: Water-view Pike Place condo near skiing with pool, hot tub, sauna & fitness room
description:
Newmark Downtown Gem

Our calendar is updated in real-time & our nightly rates are accurately displayed. Simply enter your desired dates and click 'Book Now!'

With a prime location right in the heart of downtown Seattle, this elegant, light-filled condo in Newmark Tower offers spectacular views of the surrounding skyscrapers and the blue waters of Elliott Bay. It's a beautiful space to come home to whether you're traveling for work or looking to experience the Emerald City's many charms. Within the building, you'll have access to an indoor swimming pool, a hot tub, a fitness center, a sauna, and a grilling area. If you head outside for a walk, you'll find that many of Seattle's most iconic attractions are mere steps away. Pike Place Market is just around the corner, while the surrounding blocks are home to fantastic shopping and great restaurants. You'll find the Seattle Aquarium, Waterfront Park, and the famous Seattle Great Wheel a quarter-mile west. 

Step inside to find a remodeled living space on one floor, where enormous picture windows and glass doors let in the commanding view (including a glimpse of Seattle's oldest skyscraper, the iconic Smith Tower). Make yourself at home amidst comfortable, contemporary furnishings, and kick back on the sofa in front of the wall-mounted TV. The full kitchen is equipped with polished stainless steel appliances, while the adjacent dining space features a glass-top table, plush chairs, and a stunning setting for at-home dinners overlooking the city. Bring your coffee or cocktails outside to the private balcony, leave the day's clothes to spin in the private washer/dryer, and retire to one of the bedrooms for the night - one with an en suite bathroom and another with direct access to the hallway bathroom. A sofa bed in the living room provides additional sleeping space.

Things to Know
Check-in time: 4:00 p.m.
Check-out time: 10:00 a.m.
All guests shall abide by Vacasa’s good neighbor policy and shall not engage in illegal activity. Quiet hours are from 10:00 p.m. to 8:00 a.m.
No smoking is permitted anywhere on the premises.
One of the bedrooms is separated from the living room by sliding pocket doors.

Parking notes: There is free parking available for 1 vehicle.
This rental is located on floor 21.



Damage waiver: The total cost of your reservation for this Property includes a nightly damage waiver fee, plus tax if applicable (the “Damage Waiver”). (A discount may be applied for stays of 28 nights or longer, if permitted.) The Damage Waiver covers you for up to $3,000 of accidental damage to the Property or its contents (such as furniture, fixtures, and appliances) as long as you report the incident to the host prior to checking out. The Damage Waiver fee eliminates the need for a traditional security deposit.
More information can be downloaded from the "Rental Agreement" on the checkout page.

Due to local laws or HOA requirements, guests must be at least 21 years of age to book. Guests under 21 must be accompanied by a parent or legal guardian for the duration of the reservation.

Tourist License / Licencia de turismo N °: STR-OPLI-21-000090

itemListElement.name: Snoqualmie Falls and Wineries Tour from Seattle

name: Snoqualmie Falls and Wineries Tour from Seattle
description:
We have more than 15 years experiences in tourism industry. 
We graduated hospitality & tourism at Edmond Community College. 
Holding Destination Specialist Certificate for North America, the Caribbean, and Europe.
We are flexible, and our guests satisfaction is of utmost importance to us. 
We are academic persons. 
We have been working about 4 years in Seattle area.

review.name: Fall in love with Seattle!
review.reviewBody: We had a great time on this tour with tour guide Mehrdad. He was very friendly with a great sense of humor. We visited a chocolate factory, the falls, lunch and one winnery with a bonus stop which I will not reveal. A couple from Bristol, England was on our tour who were delightful.  Glad we took the tour.

review.name: Missed this tour
review.reviewBody: Unfortunately, our tour was cancelled because we were the only two who registered. This was sad and Daniel offered ‘extras’ if we could sign up for a different day. Unfortunately, travel plans did not allow that flexibility. So we made our own tour, which was fun, but one of us had to be the designated driver 🙁.

review.name: A worthwhile tour
review.reviewBody: The itinerary was great. Our driver-guide, Slav, was fantastic. He was informative and friendly. The stop at the chocolate shop was an extra treat. The winery and distillery stops were excellent, and the falls spectacular.

review.name: Daytrip outside of Seattle - you will be happy to choose this trip!
review.reviewBody: My daughter and I did this tour in February 2025. Our guide was Daniel. We were greeted at our hotel on time and given snack bags for the trip. Daniel gave us so much history of Seattle as we made our way through the neighborhoods before setting out to the waterfalls. On our way we were told of a small family run chocolate factory and stopped by for some sweets. Yummy. When we got to the waterfalls, Daniel had walking sticks for us to borrow. He also was our photographer for many waterfall photos! The waterfalls are beautifull. We were left to walk along the path and was greated by Daniel at the end of the path. The path is slight slope down hill and very manageable. The trees were gorgeous. Daniel is extremely knowlegable of the area including the railroads, the indigenous people, the early founding families, the wineries and tasing rooms. We were given great advice and learned a lot along the way. We went to Chateau St Michelle. The grounds are pretty. They gave us a nice pour on the flights. The staff was very friendly. You can reserve an outdoor igloo ahead of time through the winery and it comes with two bottles of wine. If you are looking to get out of the city for a day and not sure where or what to do I would recommend this trip with Daniel as your guide. We had a great day.

review.name: Five stars!
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful tour with our guide, Daniel! He was very communicative leading up to it, and the pick up and drop off was smooth. He was so friendly and knowledgeable about everywhere we went. He gave wonderful advice and let us choose what we wanted during different parts of the tour. The falls were breathtaking and the whiskey and wine tastings very fun. If you are looking for a fun and relaxing day out of the city, this tour can’t be beat!

review.name: Great experience!
review.reviewBody: Slav was fantastic, he was very knowledgeable about the trip and very friendly. 10/10 would recommend. We made it back at the time we expected too.

review.name: Wonderful Tour with Daniel!
review.reviewBody: I can’t thank Oktay Tours enough as they came through last minute for the Snoqualmie Falls and Woodinville Wine Tour. The company I booked with initially cancelled due lack of interest with less than 24 hours notice. Daniel was our guide and he did an amazing job. He was very knowledgeable of the areas and had some wonderful recommendations. Can’t say enough great things about Daniel and Oktay Tours.

review.name: Great tour
review.reviewBody:
Daniel was our tour guide and he was amazing! Gave us great information and insights, helped with taking photos, and drove us to different wineries and introduced us to the staff.
I highly recommend this tour!

review.name: A lovey day at the falls and wineries
review.reviewBody: It was great to have Vlad as our driver/guide.  His knowledge of the area was helpful and he has an incredible play list that he played while driving between locations.  He was very accommodating to all of us.  (and he takes great pictures!)

review.name: Excellent experience
review.reviewBody: I am so glad that we booked this trip during our short visit to Seattle. The Falls were beautiful and we enjoyed the short walk down to the bottom of the Falls. Daniel was an excellent guide. I would highly recommend this.

itemListElement.name: Squid Fishing on Private Guided Boat in Seattle City Waterfront

name: Squid Fishing on Private Guided Boat in Seattle City Waterfront
description: Come join us during the winter squid run as we head out on our boat in search of Loligo Opalences aka Pacific Market Squid. These cephalopods are are absolute blast to catch on light tackle and even more delicious to consume. We are are the original and first professional guided squid charter based in Seattle. Be sure to check us out on Facebook or Instagram: Seattle Squid or our website.

review.name: Trip cancelled!
review.reviewBody: I booked a trip as a gift 2 months out....today I got notice that it was cancelled because the boat had to be "pulled".  I wish I had booked with another captain, because now I have one group of disappointed fisherman and I have no other alternatives!

name: Wine and Chocolate Experience
description:
Indulge your inner connoisseur!

A charming and knowledgeable guide leads you on a tasty walking tour of Seattle’s oldest neighborhood…learn about the history of Pioneer Square as you indulge in exclusive tastings and meet the makers of some of Seattle’s top chocolate and wine: Browne Family Vineyards, Intrigue Chocolate Co., and Locus Wines.

review.name: A very fun afternoon
review.reviewBody: What a fun day! Our tour guide was incredible- he knew the answer to every one of my questions. The wine was delicious, I am a local and hadn’t visited these tasting rooms and truly enjoyed them. The pairings were to die for, I especially enjoyed the truffle salami! And saving the best for last, the chocolate was unlike any chocolate I have ever had before and could not get enough of it. I had a blast with my friends and will definitely be recommending this tour to all my family and friends when they visit.

review.name: A satisfying experience
review.reviewBody: This is one of the best tours I've ever been on. The chocolate from Intrigue was second to none, and both wineries had diverse selections and pairings. It really felt like we were getting an authentic look at some of Seattle's most storied businesses, and the guide did such a good job of making us feel at home. I cannot recommend this tour enough!

review.name: Unforgettable Sensory Experience
review.reviewBody: The Wine and Chocolate Experience was so much fun, I loved walking around the city exploring some delicious local wineries and chocolatiers. Would want to do this every weekend. The tour guides were so knowledgeable and I left learning more about Seattle and the Chocolate and Wine industries.

itemListElement.name: Chihuly Garden and Glass in Seattle

name: Chihuly Garden and Glass in Seattle
description: Immerse yourself in a world where curiosity, creativity and color come to life. Throughout the Galleries, ever-changing Garden and signature Glasshouse, you’ll be inspired by artist Dale Chihuly’s innovation and passion. All guests receive complimentary digital photo downloads and access to daily Gallery Talks and live glass demonstrations. Admission includes complimentary audio tour (smartphone required).

review.name: Chihuly Museum
review.reviewBody: Loved visiting this beautiful class museum. Loved all the color that Chihuly uses just stunning. Even on a overcast day the color popped.

review.name: Great place to visit!  Highly recommend it!
review.reviewBody: We went to the Chihuly Glass Garden on 5/27/23.  This is a fabulous place.  The glass sculptures were absolutely beautiful!  The glass blowing demonstration was wonderful.  I would highly recommend people visit this place.

review.name: The Awesomeness of Chihuly
review.reviewBody: Awesome. Breathtaking. One of a kind. Worth the trip, the ticket, and the flight. Even the gift shop was lovely.

review.name: Not your everyday glass!
review.reviewBody: Chihuly glass is stunning! If you are in Seattle, book your tickets and go see the Chihuly Garden and Glass museum! The glass sculptures are beautiful and unique, and it is well-worth the 30 minutes to an hour to go through the museum and gardens. Be sure to catch one of the glass-blowing demonstrations they offer throughout the day to give you a greater appreciation of this style of art.

review.name: A Must See in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Our daughter introduced us to Dale Chihuly's work when she was an art major. As such, we have seen many exhibits of his work, but none compares to this! It is exquisite. Every room is a rainbow of colors with interesting shapes and design. This was the highlight of our trip to Seattle. It's too bad it was over run by kids there on a field trip.

review.name: Stunning
review.reviewBody: I'd never heard of this place. The only reason I went is because it was on my City Pass. It was the highlight of my trip to Seattle. The glass work here is unique and absolutely breathtaking.

review.name: Glass wonders of the World
review.reviewBody: If you only have time in Seattle o do one thing, this must be it ! The best part is that you can really get up close to the art, and really see the amazing detail of it. Really an immersive experience !

review.name: Chihuly Glass
review.reviewBody: Magnificent glass art by Dale Chihuly. Nothing like I’ve ever seen before. Some are incorporated into the lovely gardens. There is a live glass blowing exhibit also.

review.name: Beautiful Chihuly masterpieces!
review.reviewBody: Beautiful place filled with Chihuly masterpieces both inside and gardens outside.  Enjoyed reading explanations and inspiration for various themes.  We found the combined ticket with the Space Needle a good deal!

review.name: Garden Display is Lackluster
review.reviewBody: I happened to be able to see one of Chihuly's outdoor installations - this Garden is not a proper installation and it is lacking any sort of creative flair. There isn't any organizational theme other than "let's stick these tall blue staves into the ground and create a long line of glass." That's not an art installation - that's color grouping (which we've all done in kindergarten). Not worth the entrance fee. Go to the Tacoma Glass Museum instead.

review.name: Tour operator canceled two hours before event with know warning or reason!!!

Avoid!!!! Tour operator canceled two hours before no explanation didn't even notify me

I have been on hundreds of tours and I will avoid this operator like the plaque
